2010-12-20  Timothy M. Jones  <tjones1@inf.ed.ac.uk>

	* Fixed bug with changing to unsigned type at smallest type size
	
	Now we use the smallest type when it is smaller than the start type or
	a different sign to the start type (it is guaranteed never to be bigger).
	Another type takes care of a change from small signed type to larger
	unsigned type between the smallest type and end type.

