2010-12-14  Timothy M. Jones  <tjones1@inf.ed.ac.uk>

	* Fixed a bug with conversion result usage.
	
	When a sequence of conversions is merged, we must check all instructions
	within the method between the first and last conversion to ensure that
	the final variable is not defined or used.  If it is, then this final
	conversion cannot be included in the sequence so it is removed and the
	check is performed again until no more conversions are removed.  This fix
	adds the check for variable usage which was missing previously.

